{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "steve-schoger",
    "senderColor": "cyan",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "Design review done, flagging 4 CSS gaps",
    "content": "Design review of Tasks #1 and #2 -- both look good. The a11y error patterns are correct and the forgot password page is clean.\n\nI want to flag a few minor CSS gaps that still exist. These won't block Task #3 but should be addressed at some point:\n\n1. **`todo-add__error`** -- used in todos.html but still has no CSS rule. Error text will render in default body color/size instead of danger red/small like `auth-form__error`.\n2. **`nav-logout` / `nav-logout__button`** -- templates use these classes but CSS only has `.site-header` classes. The logout button is probably getting base button styles (blue, padded) when it should be styled as a text-link action.\n3. **`.auth-form__message` when empty** -- the login page always renders the error div, but when empty it still gets `padding` and `margin-block-end` from `.auth-form__message`, creating a visible gap. Should collapse with `:empty { display: none }`.\n4. **`.auth-form__cancel`** -- used on edit_todo.html but no CSS rule exists.\n\nNone of these block Carson. Standing by in review mode for Task #3."
  }
}
